cs.CR, cs.HC, cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.CY 

The paper presents a novel biometric authentication algorithm for mobile devices that is based on data collected from multiple sensors. This suggests that the paper could belong to the categories of computer security (cs.CR), human-computer interaction (cs.HC), computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV), multimedia (cs.MM), or cybernetics (cs.CY). However, given the focus on authentication and security, cs.CR is the most likely category. The emphasis on user input and flexibility also supports the possibility of cs.HC being a likely category. The use of sensors and biometric data suggests cs.CV and cs.MM as possible categories, while the focus on mobile devices and cybernetics could make cs.CY a relevant category as well.
